# Replit Deployment Checklist

## Pre-Deployment
- [ ] Repository pushed to GitHub
- [ ] Reviewed REPLIT_SETUP.md guide

## On Replit
- [ ] Imported repository to Replit
- [ ] Environment variables configured (see env.example)
  - [ ] DATABASE_URL
  - [ ] SOLANA_RPC_URL
  - [ ] NEXT_PUBLIC_SOLANA_PROGRAM_ID
  - [ ] NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL (set to your .repl.co URL)

## Setup Commands (in Replit Shell)
- [ ] npm install
- [ ] npm run db:generate
- [ ] npm run db:migrate
- [ ] npm run db:seed

## Verification
- [ ] App starts without errors
- [ ] Homepage displays pools
- [ ] Pool detail pages work
- [ ] Charts render correctly

## For Full Functionality
- [ ] Deploy Solana program (see REPLIT_SETUP.md)
- [ ] Update NEXT_PUBLIC_SOLANA_PROGRAM_ID with deployed program
- [ ] Configure Shadow Drive (optional)
- [ ] Set up PostgreSQL (recommended for production)

## Troubleshooting
If something doesn't work:
1. Check the Shell for error messages
2. Verify all environment variables are set
3. Try: npm run db:reset
4. See REPLIT_SETUP.md "Common Issues" section

